Owing to the success of the 40-year-old Nigerian, Bayode Treasure Olawunmi, who is the latest to enter into the Guinness Book Of World Records, for #LongestMarathonReadingAloud, the former vice president and business mogul, Atiku Abubakar, as well as the governor of Osun State, Rauf Aregbesola, have openly declared their support and have congratulated him for a job well done. See the tweets below: Congratulations to Olawunmi Bayode who now holds the new Guinness Record in the ‘Longest Marathon Reading Aloud’ category. pic.twitter.com/LrSCVJTwmv — Rauf Aregbesola (@raufaregbesola) March 4, 2018  Read More: Nigerian Aims To Read Himself Into Guinness Book Of World Records <img class="aligncenter wp-image-570007 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Atikus-tweet.png" alt="" width="960" height="192" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Atikus-tweet.png 590w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Atikus-tweet-487x97.png 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Atikus-tweet-320x64.png 320w" sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" />
His record-breaking feat was achieved by reading 17 books from 13 authors starting Monday, the 26th of February 2018, by 1:30 pm to Saturday, the third of March, by 3:30 pm.